[2026-03-09 14:58:37] [1d5c3289-82f5-47bd-941c-b7c9d068124c] TOOL: Bash | INPUT: {"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport re\nwith open('sample.html', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Extract the structure around a message - get the parent hierarchy\n# Find first RLrADb data-message-id element and its children structure\npattern = r'<div class=\\\"RLrADb\\\" data-message-id=\\\"[^\\\"]+\\\"[^>]*>(.*?)</div><div class=\\\"AFCrOe\\\"'\nmatches = re.findall(pattern, content, re.DOTALL)\nif matches:\n    # Simplify: find tag structure\n    msg = matches[0]\n    # Extract text content\n    texts = re.findall(r'>([^<]+)<', msg)\n    texts = [t.strip() for t in texts if t.strip()]\n    print('Text nodes in first message:')\n    for t in texts:\n        print(f'  \\\"{t}\\\"')\n\n# Check the parent structure\nprint()\nprint('=== Message container structure ===')\n# Find the class hierarchy above data-message-id\nidx = content.find('data-message-id=\\\"spaces/')\nstart = max(0, idx - 800)\nsnippet = content[start:idx]\n# Find div classes\nclasses = re.findall(r'class=\\\"([^\\\"]+)\\\"', snippet)\nprint('Parent classes (innermost last):')\nfor c in classes[-10:]:\n    print(f'  .{c}')\n\" ","description":"Analyze message structure"}
